d subtle fruit flavors while cabernet sauvignon grapes grown in california will likely produce wines that are more fruitforward but different wine regions are also often associated with the production of different grapes for example within france bordeaux is associated with red wines made primarily from cabernet sauvignon merlot and cabernet franc grapes while burgundy is associated with red wines made from the pinot noir grape use this page to find toprated wines from wine regions throughout the world and learn about each region’s winemaking profile europe france alsace bordeaux gravespessacleognan margaux pauillac pomerol saintémilion saintestéphe saintjulien sauternes and barsac burgundy beaujolais chablis côte chalonnaise côte de beaune côte de nuits mâcon champagne languedocroussillon loire provence rhône châteauneuf du pape condrieu cornas côte rotie côtes du rhone crozes hermitage gigondas and vacqueyras italy friuliveneziagiulia lombardy piedmont sicily and sardinia trentinoalto adige adige tuscany umbria veneto germany moselsaarruwer nahe pfalz rheingau rheinhessen austria portugal spain jumilla montsant navarra priorat rias rías baixas ribera del duero rioja toro valencia southern hemisphere argentina chile australia new zealand south africa united states california central coast napa sonoma oregon washington discover the best of the cellar sign up now and well email them to you every day start exploring sign up for a free exclusive membership email this email address is not in valid format please try again zip code zip code must be a number submit already a member sign in customer support   am – pm pt monday – friday helpwineaccesscom menu store about us help  faqs today’s finds today’s finds store about us help  faqs nv dieboltvallois blanc de blancs brut  pts wine  spirits  pts wine spectator nv dieboltvallois blanc de blancs brut  pts wine  spirits  pts wine spectator nv dieboltvallois blanc de blancs brut  pts wine  spirits  pts wine spectator  chatea